      <bioghist id="aspace_fbe5843473570228b9ab4fdd72594489">
         <head>Historical note</head>
         <p>The Folio Club was established by faculty wives at Duke University in the fall of 1927.
            Originally, the club consisted of 14 women who paid dues of 75 cents. Early meetings
            consisted of knitting, conversation, a book review, and tea. They evolved over time to
            adopt formal study of topics, ranging from art and history to music and political
            movements. Each member was responsible for either hosting or leading a program at least
            once per year. The club also raised money in support of local civic groups and
            organizations, including the Durham County Library, The Red Cross, hospitals and arts
            programs, and children's groups.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_3c80b621b4eea4c987a9ebf3269b77b9">
